Dear all:

If some one will ask me, what is the best quality of an average American, my
answer will be &quot;politeness &amp; soft spoken&quot;.

If you have any Indian or Chinese boss, they can yell at you whenever you do
some mistake, but in case you have any American boss - the same 'yell' will
be rephrased in a decent way and certainly you will like that.

In a recent discussion, Shri Badal Naik pointed that, we blinded followed
some 'western culture' , but we certainly missed to imitate the best quality
of west - 'politeness'.

OTN - we maintain cool in many occasions and hardly lose temper. But we are
all human beings and when 'an offensive word is directed at us in public' -
we lose temper. Things sometimes go out of control. As a moderator,  I try
my best to bring the 'peaceful discussions' to track.

Just yesterday, I was involved in a debate and surprised by the coolness of
Dr.M. Zuhdi Jasser - Head of AIFD and a doctor by profession (Arizona
state.USA).

I would request you to click the following link
http://hindtoday.com/Blogs/ViewBlogs.aspx?HTAdvtId=858&amp;HTAdvtPlaceCod...;

and read the allegation of 'Mike' and answer of  Dr.M. Zuhdi Jasser .

To the allegation of 'liar' he maintained his cool and answered in a decent
manner.

Also, look at the final reply of Mike, it was an appreciation of positive
view of Dr. Jasser and no mention of the earlier allegation.

Shri Viswas Tripathy  rightly pointed out 'not to stretch too much'.

--
At OTN we are kind of integrated with political system, where we can see
arguements Congress Vs. BJD vs BJP Vs. Samruddha Orissa - but we can always
to it in a polite &amp; cool way.

Thanks in advance for understanding

--

Manoj Padhi
