Dear Umashankar babu,

Our foundation is based on &quot;Free Voice Of Concerned Citizens&quot;.
This free voice to be expressed with careful selection of words while
conveying the same 'meaning' in a decent way.

It is not speaking for or against any individual. we all are here for
cherishing our dream of a better society. I am rich, poor, at USA, at Delhi
- doesn't matter.

I analyze this some X Government is better than Y Government based on some
logic. If you don't like you are free to analyze Y is better than X with
some logic.

I have nothing personal against Naveen any one in this forum. We just differ
in analysing news or issues. In a democracy, being from different
backgrounds, this is considered  perfectly normal.

Like you expected to be addressed in a decent manner, every one want  the
same. Our disagreements can be better worded so that in a public forum - no
one  is *embarrassed.*
**
*BTW. I don't remember hurting any one's  sentiment or using extreme words
with any civilized people. I would be grateful if any one of you can forward
me such mails to correct my 'wordings'.*
**
*Also, when I criticize some one, I remember expressing my  displeasure in a
polite way. *
**
*It is extremely difficult to practice &amp; preach the same thing for an
average person. But this is certainly  desirable.*
**
*However, irresepctive of what we practice ourself, in  a public forum  an
exreme or violent person also should be using  gentleman's language..*
**
**
thanks
Manoj Padhi

